pageContext.claim: “We’ve gotten hundreds of millions of dollars off the price of a plane that was going to be ordered.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is referring to the Lockheed F-35 program. Again, he is taking credit for something that had already been negotiated, a claim that had previously earned him Four Pinocchios. The Pentagon had already announced cost reductions of roughly $600 million before Trump had met with Lockheed’s chief executive.
